The paper discusses the integration of artificial intelligence capabilities into modern software systems, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of cloud-based machine learning services and representational state transfer architecture design suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV). The discussion of model provenance and control over model evolution suggests a focus on distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) and software engineering (cs.SE).
